00:41:33.658 --> 00:41:35.742
Too many tax dollars
to try and hide.

764
00:41:35.743 --> 00:41:38.161
and-and off-world artifacts
are too profitable

765
00:41:38.162 --> 00:41:39.955
to leave in the hands
of appointed officials.

766
00:41:39.956 --> 00:41:42.833
especially after
the Nixon thing.

767
00:41:42.834 --> 00:41:46.461
Presidents are civilians again
after eight years. so...

768
00:41:46.462 --> 00:41:50.007
so there's no longer a reason
to read them in on any of this.

769
00:41:51.884 --> 00:41:55.513
I was a part of all that
until I saw what you just saw.

770
00:41:56.431 --> 00:41:59.850
This all stops now.

771
00:41:59.851 --> 00:42:01.519
What are you gonna do?

772
00:42:02.353 --> 00:42:07.191
Full disclosure
to the whole world all at once.

773
00:42:09.861 --> 00:42:12.989
Have you considered
what effect that'll have?

774
00:42:14.157 --> 00:42:15.867
On everything?

775
00:42:16.701 --> 00:42:18.076
What...

776
00:42:18.077 --> 00:42:19.953
It's not up to me
to decide if it's...

777
00:42:19.954 --> 00:42:22.914
if it's good or bad
for people to know.

778
00:42:22.915 --> 00:42:25.792
Then how is it up to you
to decide that the right to know

779
00:42:25.793 --> 00:42:28.128
outweighs the consequences
of knowing?

780
00:42:28.129 --> 00:42:30.046
Are you saying
we leave this up to WARDEX?

781
00:42:30.047 --> 00:42:32.674
'Cause they-they've already
decided this belongs to them.

782
00:42:32.675 --> 00:42:35.260
this core truth
about the universe.

783
00:42:35.261 --> 00:42:37.764
- It's wrong.
- You can't do that.

784
00:42:38.723 --> 00:42:40.641
Think about...

785
00:42:41.934 --> 00:42:43.602
People will see them as deities.

786
00:42:43.603 --> 00:42:45.645
They'll stop believing in God.

787
00:42:45.646 --> 00:42:47.564
Well. you left the church.

788
00:42:47.565 --> 00:42:48.982
Not because I stopped believing.

789
00:42:48.983 --> 00:42:50.692
because I could no longer say
with certainty

790
00:42:50.693 --> 00:42:52.068
that God is divine.

791
00:42:52.069 --> 00:42:55.573
but I believe profoundly
that he's essential.

792
00:42:56.949 --> 00:42:58.450
He's how we define ourselves.

793
00:42:58.451 --> 00:43:01.788
He's what keeps
whole civilizations together.

794
00:43:03.039 --> 00:43:05.916
We've been raised to believe
in a supreme being.

795
00:43:05.917 --> 00:43:09.795
and now you want to show us
actual supreme beings?

796
00:43:09.796 --> 00:43:11.756
People can't handle both.

797
00:43:14.217 --> 00:43:15.842
Of course they can.

798
00:43:15.843 --> 00:43:17.470
No. they can't.

799
00:43:18.262 --> 00:43:20.431
Look at our history
with any sudden change.

800
00:43:21.265 --> 00:43:25.895
And now. with the world about
to blow up in all our faces?

801
00:43:27.104 --> 00:43:31.943
You'll get panic and-and chaos.
and God help us.

802
00:43:35.947 --> 00:43:38.241
Hugo's expecting me to check in.

803
00:43:50.086 --> 00:43:51.796
No signal.

804
00:43:53.464 --> 00:43:55.131
No signal.

805
00:43:55.132 --> 00:43:57.635
I'll try the other side
of the hill.

806
00:44:27.498 --> 00:44:28.707
Okay.

807
00:44:28.708 --> 00:44:30.041
Unlock the door!

808
00:44:30.042 --> 00:44:31.334
- What?
- Jackson. come on!

809
00:44:31.335 --> 00:44:33.254
Oh. shit. Sorry.

810
00:44:34.380 --> 00:44:36.047
Oh. sorry. sorry.

811
00:44:36.048 --> 00:44:38.801
- Okay.
- Oh. my God.

812
00:44:44.265 --> 00:44:45.974
If you answer that in French.
I swear to God

813
00:44:45.975 --> 00:44:47.517
I'm marching you
right back inside.

814
00:44:47.518 --> 00:44:49.019
Hello?

815
00:44:49.020 --> 00:44:51.021
I've been
waiting a very long time

816
00:44:51.022 --> 00:44:53.440
to meet you. Ms. Fairchild.

817
00:44:53.441 --> 00:44:55.108
Who is this?

818
00:44:55.109 --> 00:44:56.861
A friend.

819
00:44:57.778 --> 00:45:00.655
And if I'm right about you.
Margaret.

820
00:45:00.656 --> 00:45:02.073
you'd know if I wasn't.

821
00:45:02.074 --> 00:45:03.533
No. I don't... I don't know you

822
00:45:03.534 --> 00:45:05.410
any more than I know
what's happening to me.

823
00:45:05.411 --> 00:45:07.871
Very few people could
manage this as well as you.

824
00:45:07.872 --> 00:45:09.539
- I'm not managing it. I'm not.
- Who-who is that?

825
00:45:09.540 --> 00:45:12.042
I am frightened.
I'm frightened out of my wits.

826
00:45:12.043 --> 00:45:16.171
Because you're just a passenger
on your way somewhere.

827
00:45:16.172 --> 00:45:18.214
- Let us help you get there.
- Help me how?

828
00:45:18.215 --> 00:45:19.090
What do you mean?

829
00:45:19.091 --> 00:45:20.508
- Is that the FBI?
- Shh!

830
00:45:20.509 --> 00:45:21.885
We want to offer you
our protection.

831
00:45:21.886 --> 00:45:23.261
We held back on reaching out

832
00:45:23.262 --> 00:45:25.555
until after we saw
your weather report.

833
00:45:25.556 --> 00:45:26.806
You held back?

834
00:45:26.807 --> 00:45:28.016
What do you mean?
What does that mean?

835
00:45:28.017 --> 00:45:30.061
Are you gonna need a lawyer?

836
00:45:33.648 --> 00:45:36.734
Who is 873-2626?

837
00:45:38.069 --> 00:45:39.444
Since you know that number.

838
00:45:39.445 --> 00:45:42.114
you must already know
who it belongs to.

839
00:45:44.408 --> 00:45:45.785
Kellner?

840
00:45:46.577 --> 00:45:47.619
Kellner?

841
00:45:47.620 --> 00:45:49.537
All right.

842
00:45:49.538 --> 00:45:51.039
Listen carefully.

843
00:45:51.040 --> 00:45:52.290
You cannot go home.

844
00:45:52.291 --> 00:45:53.792
If you have another direction
in mind.

845
00:45:53.793 --> 00:45:56.086
even a vague inclination.
follow it.

846
00:45:56.087 --> 00:45:57.963
If we can find you by phone.
others can

847
00:45:57.964 --> 00:45:59.839
- find you in the world.
- No. it's too late.

848
00:45:59.840 --> 00:46:01.216
They...
Uh. they already found me.

849
00:46:01.217 --> 00:46:04.052
Hang up immediately.
Destroy your phone.

850
00:46:04.053 --> 00:46:05.470
How will you find me?

851
00:46:05.471 --> 00:46:06.930
I have every confidence
you'll find us.

852
00:46:06.931 --> 00:46:08.140
Do it now.

853
00:46:09.600 --> 00:46:12.812
Wait. wait. What are you...
Wh-What are you doing?!

854
00:46:14.105 --> 00:46:15.397
Back up over the phone.

855
00:46:15.398 --> 00:46:16.815
- What?
- Back up!

856
00:46:16.816 --> 00:46:18.441
Come on. -Okay. I'd like
to point out that I'm being

857
00:46:18.442 --> 00:46:21.069
extremely cool here
and that I'm rolling with it.

858
00:46:21.070 --> 00:46:23.280
and that was a $600 phone.

859
00:46:24.115 --> 00:46:26.116
Well. it's still a $600 phone
'cause you missed it.

860
00:46:26.117 --> 00:46:27.742
Jackson. pull forward
till you hear the crunch.

861
00:46:27.743 --> 00:46:28.953
- Come on.
- Sorry.

862
00:46:33.165 --> 00:46:35.583
Oh. my God. you missed it again.
Oh. my God.

863
00:46:35.584 --> 00:46:37.795
- Okay.
- What?

864
00:46:41.424 --> 00:46:42.883
Okay.

865
00:46:44.218 --> 00:46:46.971
Pull forward. Go. go. go.

866
00:46:48.222 --> 00:46:50.266
Keep going. Keep going.

867
00:46:59.483 --> 00:47:01.609
Okay. Okay.

868
00:47:01.610 --> 00:47:05.155
- Okay. let's go. Let's go.
- Uh... wh-where?

869
00:47:05.156 --> 00:47:06.656
- North.
- Why?

870
00:47:06.657 --> 00:47:08.116
Because that's where
Daniel Kellner is.

871
00:47:08.117 --> 00:47:09.534
Oh. my God.

872
00:47:09.535 --> 00:47:11.327
Who is this dude?
Is he some guy from your past

873
00:47:11.328 --> 00:47:12.996
- that you never told me about?
- I don't know. Jackson.

874
00:47:12.997 --> 00:47:14.247
- Or what is it?
- You're giving me a headache.

875
00:47:14.248 --> 00:47:15.206
I don't know
what I'm doing here.

876
00:47:15.207 --> 00:47:16.499
I don't know who he is.

877
00:47:16.500 --> 00:47:18.126
I just know
he's someplace north.

878
00:47:18.127 --> 00:47:19.210
That's all I know. okay?

879
00:47:19.211 --> 00:47:20.963
Oh. my God. What is that sound?

880
00:47:23.090 --> 00:47:25.425
- Your hailstorm.
- Wow.

881
00:47:25.426 --> 00:47:26.801
Weather Shimmy?

882
00:47:26.802 --> 00:47:29.180
Just drive. Just drive.

883
00:48:17.603 --> 00:48:20.231
You got Kellner on 2626.

884
00:48:21.816 --> 00:48:23.399
Look at the video
I just sent you.

885
00:48:23.400 --> 00:48:25.069
DANIEL
Okay. hold on.

886
00:48:31.450 --> 00:48:32.700
Yeah. So?

887
00:48:32.701 --> 00:48:34.869
She's the one
we've been waiting for.

888
00:48:34.870 --> 00:48:37.247
Her? Why?

889
00:48:37.248 --> 00:48:39.541
Did you not hear her?

890
00:48:39.542 --> 00:48:41.126
Yeah. I heard her.

891
00:48:41.127 --> 00:48:42.502
And you still ask why?

892
00:48:42.503 --> 00:48:44.420
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know"?

893
00:48:44.421 --> 00:48:46.423
That's all she had to say?

894
00:48:47.591 --> 00:48:49.884
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know"?

895
00:48:49.885 --> 00:48:51.219
That's what she said?

896
00:48:51.220 --> 00:48:53.055
You didn't hear it?

897
00:48:54.431 --> 00:48:55.723
We all heard it.

898
00:48:55.724 --> 00:48:58.101
We couldn't understand it.
It's not English.

899
00:48:58.102 --> 00:48:59.853
Of course it is.

900
00:48:59.854 --> 00:49:01.688
I'm listening to it right now.

901
00:49:01.689 --> 00:49:03.606
I'm sending you to Kansas City.
where she's from.

902
00:49:03.607 --> 00:49:05.692
We'll get a car to you.
Leave tonight. -Hey. wait.

903
00:49:05.693 --> 00:49:07.318
- Wait a second. Wait a second.
- Do not travel by day.

904
00:49:07.319 --> 00:49:08.611
You're not hearing it?
It's-it's perfectly clear.

905
00:49:08.612 --> 00:49:09.946
Detour past tollbooths
and turnpikes.

906
00:49:09.947 --> 00:49:11.197
Hey. listen to me.

907
00:49:11.198 --> 00:49:12.615
Have you played this
to other people?

908
00:49:12.616 --> 00:49:14.492
Stay with me.

909
00:49:14.493 --> 00:49:17.287
A motel room key will be
in the car with directions.

910
00:49:17.288 --> 00:49:19.289
Santiago will retrieve you
in the morning.

911
00:49:19.290 --> 00:49:21.708
By then. I'll know
what comes next.

912
00:49:21.709 --> 00:49:24.460
Hugo. you're scaring
the shit out of me.

913
00:49:24.461 --> 00:49:28.298
There are two of you. Daniel.

914
00:49:28.299 --> 00:49:31.676
There's always been
just the two of you.

915
00:52:26.894 --> 00:52:28.644
Hello. Jane.

916
00:52:28.645 --> 00:52:30.481
Please.

917
00:52:31.732 --> 00:52:33.776
Have a seat.

918
00:52:39.281 --> 00:52:42.033
Where are you right now. Jane?

919
00:52:42.034 --> 00:52:43.827
What is your location?

920
00:52:44.828 --> 00:52:47.498
- I don't know.
- Relax. please.

921
00:52:50.584 --> 00:52:53.462
- Who are you?
- I'll ask the questions.

922
00:52:54.254 --> 00:52:56.298
Are you still with
Daniel Kellner?

923
00:53:02.221 --> 00:53:03.680
He's outside.

924
00:53:07.184 --> 00:53:08.894
Where were you last night?

925
00:53:18.153 --> 00:53:20.947
- BP's high but holding: 156/94.
- O2's decent at 96.

926
00:53:20.948 --> 00:53:22.949
- but sodium's climbing.
- Heart rate's hot. too-- 118.

927
00:53:22.950 --> 00:53:24.325
- Potassium's borderline. too.
- Jane!

928
00:53:24.326 --> 00:53:25.953
- Stand by. Ringer's.
- Jane!

929
00:53:26.912 --> 00:53:28.413
Jane!

930
00:53:28.414 --> 00:53:30.874
Where were you last night?

931
00:53:31.834 --> 00:53:35.044
Monastery of St. Clare
of the Dawn.

932
00:53:35.045 --> 00:53:37.255
Monastery St. Clare?

933
00:53:37.256 --> 00:53:38.714
Of course.

934
00:53:38.715 --> 00:53:41.759
I remember St. Clare
from my Sunday school.

935
00:53:41.760 --> 00:53:43.845
She was too sick to go
to midnight Mass.

936
00:53:43.846 --> 00:53:46.556
and she had a vision
of it instead.

937
00:53:46.557 --> 00:53:49.393
She was in two places at once.
like me.

938
00:53:51.770 --> 00:53:53.896
Monastery of St. Clare. Got it.

939
00:53:53.897 --> 00:53:55.940
13 miles southeast
of the District.

940
00:53:55.941 --> 00:53:58.735
When you left.
which way did you drive?

941
00:54:02.281 --> 00:54:03.781
I don't know.

942
00:54:03.782 --> 00:54:05.409
Was the sun up?

943
00:54:08.287 --> 00:54:09.704
Yes.

944
00:54:09.705 --> 00:54:12.249
Did you drive into it
or away from it?

945
00:54:15.419 --> 00:54:17.337
It was on the right.

946
00:54:19.256 --> 00:54:20.923
I don't like you.

947
00:54:20.924 --> 00:54:22.800
Not required.

948
00:54:22.801 --> 00:54:24.010
Sun on the right.

949
00:54:24.011 --> 00:54:26.095
Sun on the right--
they're headed due north.

950
00:54:26.096 --> 00:54:27.388
possibly northwest.

951
00:54:27.389 --> 00:54:29.223
Could be on 27. 18
or the interstate.

952
00:54:29.224 --> 00:54:30.641
Interstate not likely.

953
00:54:30.642 --> 00:54:32.393
Focus on frontage roads
or county highways.

954
00:54:32.394 --> 00:54:35.104
Did you pass a street sign?

955
00:54:35.105 --> 00:54:36.772
Yes.

956
00:54:36.773 --> 00:54:38.441
What did it say?

957
00:54:42.613 --> 00:54:45.823
"Silver Spring: 120 miles."

958
00:54:45.824 --> 00:54:48.451
Street sign.
"Silver Spring: 120 miles."

959
00:54:48.452 --> 00:54:51.078
I've got half
a dozen towns off the 26.

960
00:54:51.079 --> 00:54:54.499
Silver Hollow. Oakshade.
Ironmere. Stonemont...

961
00:54:54.500 --> 00:54:56.459
Try for more details. Jane.

962
00:54:56.460 --> 00:54:58.211
What else did you pass?

963
00:55:00.005 --> 00:55:01.172
A river.

964
00:55:01.173 --> 00:55:02.757
Passed a river.

965
00:55:02.758 --> 00:55:05.010
Did you see a sign for a town
after that?

966
00:55:07.179 --> 00:55:09.473
- Yes.
- What did it say?

967
00:55:13.894 --> 00:55:15.478
S-Sykesville.

968
00:55:15.479 --> 00:55:18.482
- Sykesville.
- Sykesville.

969
00:55:19.399 --> 00:55:21.817
Field is narrowed.
Track and converge.

970
00:55:21.818 --> 00:55:24.654
Charlie 27. take the lead.
You're four miles out.

971
00:55:24.655 --> 00:55:26.989
Maintain maximum legal speed.

972
00:55:26.990 --> 00:55:29.951
How soon after you saw the sign
did you make a turn?

973
00:55:29.952 --> 00:55:31.744
- A few minutes.
- Few minutes.

974
00:55:31.745 --> 00:55:33.788
Did you turn right or left?

975
00:55:33.789 --> 00:55:35.456
- Right.
- Right.

976
00:55:35.457 --> 00:55:38.251
Do you remember
the name of the road?

977
00:55:38.252 --> 00:55:39.544
No.

978
00:55:39.545 --> 00:55:41.672
Do you remember anything
about the road?

979
00:55:50.180 --> 00:55:52.098
It was a dirt road.

980
00:55:52.099 --> 00:55:53.516
Dirt road.

981
00:55:53.517 --> 00:55:55.351
Ash Hollow Road.
three and a quarter miles

982
00:55:55.352 --> 00:55:57.645
outside Sykesville. dead end.

983
00:55:57.646 --> 00:55:59.313
Farmhouse at the end.

984
00:55:59.314 --> 00:56:00.856
And found it.

985
00:56:00.857 --> 00:56:02.191
Ash Hollow Road.

986
00:56:02.192 --> 00:56:04.570
Target is a farmhouse.

987
00:56:11.285 --> 00:56:13.578
You've done very well. Jane.

988
00:56:13.579 --> 00:56:16.122
A service to your country.

989
00:56:16.123 --> 00:56:19.625
But I have to ask you
one more thing.

990
00:56:19.626 --> 00:56:23.754
If we can't find Daniel
or we miss him again.

991
00:56:23.755 --> 00:56:26.382
you may need
to stop him yourself

992
00:56:26.383 --> 00:56:28.552
any way you can.

993
00:56:34.766 --> 00:56:36.851
Hang on. BP just tanked.
88 on 62.

994
00:56:36.852 --> 00:56:38.811
Uh. heart rate's dropping--
down to 59.

995
00:56:38.812 --> 00:56:42.064
Uh. O2 is 93 and falling. 91.

996
00:56:46.236 --> 00:56:48.321
92 on 60 and holding.
O2's still dropping. though.

997
00:56:48.322 --> 00:56:49.572
Let's start bagging.

998
00:56:49.573 --> 00:56:50.906
Make sure you secure the airway.

999
00:56:50.907 --> 00:56:53.909
High 80s. Keep going.

1000
00:56:53.910 --> 00:56:55.745
Get away!

1001
00:57:01.126 --> 00:57:03.003
Jane.

1002
00:57:03.795 --> 00:57:07.173
What Daniel is trying to do
is wrong.

1003
00:57:07.174 --> 00:57:09.425
It's dangerous.

1004
00:57:09.426 --> 00:57:13.096
It would tip the balance in
an already destabilized world.

1005
00:57:14.097 --> 00:57:15.181
Yes.

1006
00:57:15.182 --> 00:57:17.558
Jane. could you stop him
if you had to?

1007
00:57:17.559 --> 00:57:20.604
No. No.

1008
00:57:23.398 --> 00:57:26.400
"Father. if you be willing.

1009
00:57:26.401 --> 00:57:29.445
"let this cup pass me by.

1010
00:57:29.446 --> 00:57:32.782
Yet not as I will.
but as you will."

1011
00:57:32.783 --> 00:57:35.452
And what did Christ say next?

1012
00:57:36.787 --> 00:57:39.331
"By my will.
thine will be done."

1013
00:57:40.123 --> 00:57:43.834
If the moment comes.
I'll be with you.

1014
00:57:43.835 --> 00:57:45.836
and you'll act. Jane.

1015
00:57:45.837 --> 00:57:49.758
out of love for Daniel.
out of love for the human race.

1016
00:57:52.803 --> 00:57:54.763
Now look around the room.

1017
00:57:55.889 --> 00:57:57.182
Slowly.

1018
00:58:00.602 --> 00:58:01.978
Left to right.

1019
00:58:05.148 --> 00:58:06.733
