01:23:01.435 --> 01:23:03.477
Yeah. but-but... but you know.
You know.

1273
01:23:03.478 --> 01:23:05.188
I mean. you've been driving
like a maniac

1274
01:23:05.189 --> 01:23:06.606
the last few days. you know.

1275
01:23:06.607 --> 01:23:08.482
- How do you know that?
- I just know things.

1276
01:23:08.483 --> 01:23:10.151
It's just. something happened
to me a couple of days ago.

1277
01:23:10.152 --> 01:23:12.195
and now I-I know things.

1278
01:23:12.196 --> 01:23:13.487
Things I don't really
want to know.

1279
01:23:13.488 --> 01:23:14.906
and all the things
I do want to know.

1280
01:23:14.907 --> 01:23:16.157
I don't really know at all.

1281
01:23:16.158 --> 01:23:17.533
so I've just been
kind of rolling with it.

1282
01:23:17.534 --> 01:23:19.410
You know. like...
Oh. wow. you were in jail?

1283
01:23:19.411 --> 01:23:20.953
- That must have been so...
- Hey. hey!

1284
01:23:20.954 --> 01:23:22.955
You see what I mean?

1285
01:23:22.956 --> 01:23:24.957
It's crazy. It's crazy.

1286
01:23:24.958 --> 01:23:29.004
I look at somebody.
and I just drop in on them.

1287
01:23:29.755 --> 01:23:32.590
It's like. for a few seconds.
I am them.

1288
01:23:32.591 --> 01:23:34.383
I see the things
that they've lived.

1289
01:23:34.384 --> 01:23:36.677
It's just like
it's all happening to me. too.

1290
01:23:36.678 --> 01:23:37.887
You know. like-like...

1291
01:23:37.888 --> 01:23:39.513
like right now
your shoulder's killing you.

1292
01:23:39.514 --> 01:23:41.390
Yeah. and you-you just
want to yell.

1293
01:23:41.391 --> 01:23:42.850
- "Keep your eyes on the road!"
- Keep your eyes on the road!

1294
01:23:42.851 --> 01:23:44.644
I know. and you can't stop
thinking about Jane.

1295
01:23:44.645 --> 01:23:46.020
and Jane should be back
at the Monastery St. Clare.

1296
01:23:46.021 --> 01:23:47.396
- You're absolutely right.
- Jane?

1297
01:23:47.397 --> 01:23:50.191
But then yesterday.
I'm driving with Jackson.

1298
01:23:50.192 --> 01:23:52.235
and I flashed on you
without seeing you.

1299
01:23:52.236 --> 01:23:53.903
It was so strong.

1300
01:23:53.904 --> 01:23:55.404
I dropped right in on you

1301
01:23:55.405 --> 01:23:56.948
without even needing
to look at you. and that was

1302
01:23:56.949 --> 01:23:59.033
the first time that crazy shit
has ever happened to me.

1303
01:23:59.034 --> 01:24:00.743
How long you been able
to do this?

1304
01:24:00.744 --> 01:24:01.994
Since yesterday.

1305
01:24:01.995 --> 01:24:03.579
Since the bird.

1306
01:24:03.580 --> 01:24:05.248
- What bird?
- This-this bird.

1307
01:24:05.249 --> 01:24:06.791
Flew in through my window.

1308
01:24:06.792 --> 01:24:08.960
It was beautiful. I looked
at it. and then it-it...

1309
01:24:08.961 --> 01:24:10.044
Was it a cardinal?

1310
01:24:10.045 --> 01:24:11.337
Holy sh... How the...

1311
01:24:11.338 --> 01:24:12.713
You're freaking me the fuck out.

1312
01:24:18.929 --> 01:24:20.304
I was 20. I was in college.

1313
01:24:20.305 --> 01:24:22.265
You were flunking out.
basically. right?

1314
01:24:22.266 --> 01:24:23.599
Yeah. I-I was pretty smart.

1315
01:24:23.600 --> 01:24:25.142
You were. but it was
the partying.

1316
01:24:25.143 --> 01:24:26.227
It was the partying
and the drugs.

1317
01:24:26.228 --> 01:24:27.687
I mean. ketamine? Come on. dude.

1318
01:24:27.688 --> 01:24:29.146
- Could you please stop?
- Sorry. I'm stopping.

1319
01:24:29.147 --> 01:24:30.398
- I was 20. I was in college.
- Yes.

1320
01:24:30.399 --> 01:24:32.984
Uh. it was dark. I-I was in bed.

1321
01:24:32.985 --> 01:24:35.486
and I dreamed that
something was watching me.

1322
01:24:35.487 --> 01:24:37.196
I woke up.
and there was this bird.

1323
01:24:37.197 --> 01:24:38.572
- It was a cardinal.
- In the window.

1324
01:24:38.573 --> 01:24:40.700
and it-it looked at me.
and after that.

1325
01:24:40.701 --> 01:24:41.993
everything just changed.

1326
01:24:41.994 --> 01:24:44.745
I saw things:
context. patterns. artifacting.

1327
01:24:44.746 --> 01:24:46.163
I could see it all.

1328
01:24:46.164 --> 01:24:48.249
Arrays and conditionals
just appeared in my head...

1329
01:24:48.250 --> 01:24:49.875
Fully solved. "If P. then Q."

1330
01:24:49.876 --> 01:24:51.252
Exactly. Solved equations

1331
01:24:51.253 --> 01:24:52.670
- without even thinking...
- And you could read

1332
01:24:52.671 --> 01:24:54.171
eight-bit binary data
like it was English.

1333
01:24:54.172 --> 01:24:55.298
- like it was nothing.
- Yeah.

1334
01:24:55.299 --> 01:24:56.590
How do you know all this?

1335
01:24:56.591 --> 01:24:58.134
I don't. You do.

1336
01:24:58.135 --> 01:24:59.343
God. you hated it.

1337
01:24:59.344 --> 01:25:01.178
- It was a curse.
- Yeah.

1338
01:25:01.179 --> 01:25:02.805
I couldn't relate to anybody.

1339
01:25:02.806 --> 01:25:04.682
I lost every friend I ever had
because I-I couldn't stand

1340
01:25:04.683 --> 01:25:06.434
to be around people.

1341
01:25:06.435 --> 01:25:08.312
Until you met Jane.

1342
01:25:11.523 --> 01:25:13.274
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know."

1343
01:25:13.275 --> 01:25:15.067
- What?
- That's what you said on TV.

1344
01:25:15.068 --> 01:25:16.736
They said I was
talking nonsense.

1345
01:25:16.737 --> 01:25:18.070
I understood every word.

1346
01:25:18.071 --> 01:25:19.697
What happened to us?

1347
01:25:19.698 --> 01:25:21.699
Oh. my God.

1348
01:25:23.952 --> 01:25:25.412
Who is it?!

1349
01:25:27.956 --> 01:25:29.165
Boyd. stop!

1350
01:25:29.166 --> 01:25:30.459
Boyd!

1351
01:25:39.676 --> 01:25:40.719
Shit.

1352
01:25:41.553 --> 01:25:43.346
We got to jump! We got to bail!

1353
01:25:43.347 --> 01:25:45.432
I can't!
I'm standing on the brakes!

1354
01:25:49.311 --> 01:25:51.396
Oh. my God! Oh. my God!

1355
01:25:53.315 --> 01:25:54.649
No. no. no. no. no. no. no!

1356
01:25:56.985 --> 01:25:58.653
He's backing up! Get out now!

1357
01:26:12.000 --> 01:26:14.211
All right. all right!

1358
01:26:22.469 --> 01:26:24.221
Get to the ladder!

1359
01:26:29.810 --> 01:26:32.019
Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1360
01:26:32.020 --> 01:26:33.396
Okay.

1361
01:27:09.224 --> 01:27:11.308
Go! Jump!

1362
01:27:24.156 --> 01:27:25.907
You got to jump!

1363
01:27:26.908 --> 01:27:28.493
Jump! Now!

1364
01:28:02.986 --> 01:28:04.529
Oh. my God.

1365
01:28:12.412 --> 01:28:15.457
I can't breathe.
I can't breathe.

1366
01:28:16.208 --> 01:28:17.709
I can't breathe.

1367
01:28:18.793 --> 01:28:21.045
- It's okay. It's okay.
- I can't breathe.

1368
01:28:21.046 --> 01:28:22.796
I think you're having
a panic attack. -Oh. my God.

1369
01:28:22.797 --> 01:28:24.965
- It's okay. It's okay.
- Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1370
01:28:24.966 --> 01:28:26.842
- It's okay. I'm used to 'em.
- My hands.

1371
01:28:26.843 --> 01:28:28.677
- We're okay.
- It's like my dad.

1372
01:28:28.678 --> 01:28:30.137
- It's like my dad. My hands.
- No. no. no. No. no. no. no.

1373
01:28:30.138 --> 01:28:32.348
It's like Parkinson's.
It's like Parkinson's.

1374
01:28:32.349 --> 01:28:33.641
It's not the same thing.
It's not that.

1375
01:28:33.642 --> 01:28:35.142
Yes. it is. It's the same.

1376
01:28:35.143 --> 01:28:37.311
No. he couldn't control it.
I can't control it.

1377
01:28:37.312 --> 01:28:38.812
- I can't control it.
- You can.

1378
01:28:38.813 --> 01:28:41.398
Oh. my God.
I ran away from him.

1379
01:28:41.399 --> 01:28:44.485
I didn't want to be around
him anymore. -No. no. no. Stop.

1380
01:28:44.486 --> 01:28:46.362
- I want this gone!
- Okay.

1381
01:28:46.363 --> 01:28:49.073
I just want it gone!
I want it gone!

1382
01:28:49.074 --> 01:28:51.825
I want it gone! I just have
no mind of my own anymore!

1383
01:28:51.826 --> 01:28:53.994
Okay. stop! Stop!
Stop talking! Stop.

1384
01:28:53.995 --> 01:28:54.995
Give me your hands.

1385
01:28:54.996 --> 01:28:56.455
- Okay. look at me.
- No. no. no.

1386
01:28:56.456 --> 01:28:57.748
- Look at me.
- I-I'm gonna see things.

1387
01:28:57.749 --> 01:28:59.333
- I'm gonna see things. Please.
- Okay.

1388
01:28:59.334 --> 01:29:00.626
Breathe through your nose.
Breathe through your nose.

1389
01:29:02.254 --> 01:29:04.004
That's it. Okay.

1390
01:29:04.005 --> 01:29:06.090
I can't feel my hands.

1391
01:29:06.091 --> 01:29:07.883
Okay. Okay.

1392
01:29:07.884 --> 01:29:09.510
Okay. give me your hands.
Come on.

1393
01:29:09.511 --> 01:29:11.512
Come on. Put your hands there.

1394
01:29:11.513 --> 01:29:13.514
Feel that. Okay. you feel that?

1395
01:29:13.515 --> 01:29:15.266
I'm here. I'm here.

1396
01:29:15.267 --> 01:29:16.684
We're here.

1397
01:29:16.685 --> 01:29:18.520
- We're okay.
- Okay.

1398
01:29:19.479 --> 01:29:21.105
- We're okay.
- We're okay.

1399
01:29:21.106 --> 01:29:23.315
We're okay.

1400
01:29:23.316 --> 01:29:26.193
We're okay now. You're okay.

1401
01:29:30.365 --> 01:29:32.491
We're okay.

1402
01:29:32.492 --> 01:29:34.034
Okay.

1403
01:29:38.498 --> 01:29:40.542
Thank you.

1404
01:29:43.169 --> 01:29:45.713
Kellner called in from a gas
station outside Mount Leonard.

1405
01:29:45.714 --> 01:29:47.047
I'll meet Santiago and his crew.

1406
01:29:47.048 --> 01:29:49.384
We can be there
in a couple hours.

1407
01:29:51.970 --> 01:29:53.929
H-Hugo?

1408
01:29:53.930 --> 01:29:55.556
Could everyone leave
the staging area

1409
01:29:55.557 --> 01:29:56.932
for a minute. please?

1410
01:29:56.933 --> 01:30:00.102
- Now. please! Out!
- Yeah. Okay. let's go.

1411
01:30:06.276 --> 01:30:07.986
Hello. Hugo.

1412
01:30:13.491 --> 01:30:15.619
Noah. please.

1413
01:30:16.411 --> 01:30:18.662
It's terribly misguided for you
to dive with that thing.

1414
01:30:18.663 --> 01:30:20.664
It's not a magic wand.

1415
01:30:20.665 --> 01:30:22.583
And it's not a weapon.
but it has functions

1416
01:30:22.584 --> 01:30:25.586
very far beyond
your limited use of it.

1417
01:30:25.587 --> 01:30:30.090
Kellner was an experiencer.
wasn't he?

1418
01:30:30.091 --> 01:30:32.259
That's why
I couldn't dive on him.

1419
01:30:32.260 --> 01:30:34.553
Yes.

1420
01:30:34.554 --> 01:30:36.598
He was.

1421
01:30:38.016 --> 01:30:42.479
And In Vivo 17
told you to recruit him?

1422
01:30:43.480 --> 01:30:45.439
Not in any way you'd understand.

1423
01:30:45.440 --> 01:30:46.982
If this is all their plan. Hugo.

1424
01:30:46.983 --> 01:30:49.693
you can be sure it's
in their interests. not ours.

1425
01:30:49.694 --> 01:30:52.279
That's a very lonely way
to look at the world.

1426
01:30:52.280 --> 01:30:53.697
No. don't condescend to me.

1427
01:30:53.698 --> 01:30:55.157
I'm listening to you. Noah.

1428
01:30:55.158 --> 01:30:57.451
Something I've learned
quite a bit about.

1429
01:30:57.452 --> 01:30:59.119
From your friends?

1430
01:30:59.120 --> 01:31:00.496
Yes.

1431
01:31:00.497 --> 01:31:03.624
They regard empathy
as an evolutionary advantage.

1432
01:31:03.625 --> 01:31:06.126
as the foremost
evolutionary advantage.

1433
01:31:06.127 --> 01:31:10.214
in fact. the core
of animate existence.

1434
01:31:10.215 --> 01:31:12.591
Our rejection
of this understanding

1435
01:31:12.592 --> 01:31:14.969
is leading us to our extinction.

1436
01:31:15.762 --> 01:31:18.973
And is your bleeding heart
why you helped it escape?

1437
01:31:20.767 --> 01:31:22.476
Five years ago.

1438
01:31:22.477 --> 01:31:24.646
That was you. wasn't it?

1439
01:31:26.189 --> 01:31:27.649
Yes.

1440
01:31:28.650 --> 01:31:31.610
The utter insanity
of that act aside.

1441
01:31:31.611 --> 01:31:33.862
how could you lie to me
for five years

1442
01:31:33.863 --> 01:31:35.489
every time you walked
through the door?

1443
01:31:35.490 --> 01:31:38.660
Everything you said to me.
it was all diversion.

1444
01:31:40.203 --> 01:31:43.664
When precisely did you lose
your bearings?

1445
01:31:43.665 --> 01:31:46.167
Around the time you lost yours.

1446
01:31:48.503 --> 01:31:50.171
When you lost her.

1447
01:31:54.259 --> 01:31:57.261
You lost her and almost
immediately were lost to me.

1448
01:31:57.262 --> 01:31:58.554
Because you shut down.

1449
01:31:58.555 --> 01:32:00.013
Do not presume to know me.

1450
01:32:00.014 --> 01:32:01.515
When she died.
you reduced everyone

1451
01:32:01.516 --> 01:32:03.267
to need-to-know. including me.

1452
01:32:03.268 --> 01:32:04.518
Because you were very clear.

1453
01:32:04.519 --> 01:32:05.894
All you needed to know was them.

1454
01:32:05.895 --> 01:32:08.355
and they are not knowable.
not by us.

1455
01:32:08.356 --> 01:32:10.899
They will be.

1456
01:32:10.900 --> 01:32:13.068
In Vivo 17 is nonhuman

1457
01:32:13.069 --> 01:32:14.945
but nearer to God. Noah.
than you or I.

1458
01:32:14.946 --> 01:32:17.115
You don't need to fear them.

1459
01:32:18.116 --> 01:32:19.950
I fear us.

1460
01:32:19.951 --> 01:32:23.078
The entire reason WARDEX exists
is because of our knowledge.

1461
01:32:23.079 --> 01:32:27.249
certain that the human race
cannot accept what we know.

1462
01:32:27.250 --> 01:32:29.334
That truth will upend
all established order

1463
01:32:29.335 --> 01:32:30.586
across the entire world.

1464
01:32:30.587 --> 01:32:33.088
The archive Kellner stole
is a virus

1465
01:32:33.089 --> 01:32:37.551
against which
the world has zero immunity.

1466
01:32:37.552 --> 01:32:39.928
I have spent 35 years
protecting...

1467
01:32:39.929 --> 01:32:41.263
Your own wealth and power--

1468
01:32:41.264 --> 01:32:43.307
that's all
you've been protecting.

1469
01:32:43.308 --> 01:32:46.059
Noah. Noah.

1470
01:32:46.060 --> 01:32:48.228
There is an essential need
in all of us to believe

1471
01:32:48.229 --> 01:32:51.732
and an equal need
to be believed.

1472
01:32:51.733 --> 01:32:53.942
You've violated
every standard of evidence.

1473
01:32:53.943 --> 01:32:55.569
You've infantilized anyone

1474
01:32:55.570 --> 01:32:58.322
who only wanted to understand
what they've witnessed.

1475
01:32:58.323 --> 01:33:01.241
You've brutally stifled
their questions.

1476
01:33:01.242 --> 01:33:04.036
shouted them down.
ridiculed and shamed

1477
01:33:04.037 --> 01:33:05.913
and overridden them
for the crime

1478
01:33:05.914 --> 01:33:08.040
of simply being astonished.

1479
01:33:08.041 --> 01:33:10.834
We believe the believers
and then deny the world

1480
01:33:10.835 --> 01:33:12.586
the chance to believe them. too.

1481
01:33:12.587 --> 01:33:15.297
But people keep wondering.
encountering the unknown.

1482
01:33:15.298 --> 01:33:17.090
telling others
of their experiences.

1483
01:33:17.091 --> 01:33:19.635
They are starved for the truth.

1484
01:33:19.636 --> 01:33:23.096
This 79-year terror campaign

1485
01:33:23.097 --> 01:33:26.809
of obfuscation. lies
and cover-up has to end!

1486
01:33:26.810 --> 01:33:28.769
We're ready to show you
a demonstration.

1487
01:33:28.770 --> 01:33:31.396
- Get out! Get out!
- Sorry. sir. we have...

1488
01:33:31.397 --> 01:33:33.608
Turn around and get out now!

1489
01:33:38.571 --> 01:33:41.782
Pull up the 12 who didn't
show up to work yesterday.

1490
01:33:41.783 --> 01:33:44.785
I need faces
who are with him right now.

1491
01:33:44.786 --> 01:33:47.496
- Her.
- Grace Zhao. neuro-services.

1492
01:33:47.497 --> 01:33:49.248
- Him.
- Nathan Twinning.

1493
01:33:49.249 --> 01:33:50.499
Hugo's chief aide.

1494
01:33:50.500 --> 01:33:52.334
Got a back door
into their mobile providers.

1495
01:33:52.335 --> 01:33:54.128
Hang on.

1496
01:33:56.965 --> 01:34:01.761
They shut down their phones
last night... right here.

1497
01:34:02.804 --> 01:34:04.471
I'll project their routes ahead
to overlap.

1498
01:34:04.472 --> 01:34:07.558
I can give you the AI model
within a quarter-mile radius.

1499
01:34:15.984 --> 01:34:18.820
Sister Maura. Sister.

1500
01:34:26.828 --> 01:34:28.453
Jane?

1501
01:34:28.454 --> 01:34:29.872
Where are you. Jane?

1502
01:34:32.667 --> 01:34:34.209
Does God love us?

1503
01:34:34.210 --> 01:34:37.504
I don't mean. does he love us?
I know he does.

1504
01:34:37.505 --> 01:34:41.174
Does he love only us?

1505
01:34:41.175 --> 01:34:43.427
'Cause Genesis says that
we're his supreme creation.

1506
01:34:43.428 --> 01:34:46.471
but do you think
it's possible that...

1507
01:34:46.472 --> 01:34:48.016
On Earth.

1508
01:34:49.267 --> 01:34:50.517
What?

1509
01:34:50.518 --> 01:34:52.019
Genesis.

1510
01:34:52.020 --> 01:34:56.941
It says we are God's
supreme creation on Earth.

1511
01:35:05.825 --> 01:35:08.036
Do you think
there could be others?

1512
01:35:09.579 --> 01:35:11.705
Yes.

1513
01:35:11.706 --> 01:35:13.290
I would think so.

1514
01:35:13.291 --> 01:35:17.044
Why would he make
such a vast universe.

1515
01:35:17.045 --> 01:35:21.299
yet save it only for us?

1516
01:35:22.175 --> 01:35:27.346
If you found out
we weren't alone. if...

1517
01:35:27.347 --> 01:35:31.184
if someone showed you.
proved it to you...

1518
01:35:32.852 --> 01:35:35.145
...would that frighten you?

1519
01:35:35.146 --> 01:35:38.065
